  "prompt": "Does a user always need to keep the data \u2018ON\u2019 for outgoing/incoming calls on Jio network?",
  "response": "On the Jio network, it is not necessary to keep mobile data turned on for making or receiving calls. Jio uses Voice over LTE (VoLTE) technology, which enables voice calls over the 4G LTE network. As long as your device supports VoLTE and is properly configured, you should be able to make and receive calls without having your mobile data switched on. However, keeping the VoLTE settings activated is essential, and some devices might require mobile data to be on to maintain a stable VoLTE connection. Regardless, actual data usage is not necessary for regular voice calls on VoLTE networks.",
